<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189873>
    bibo:endPage "35" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "2211" ;
    dc:creator "Heinicke, Matthew P.; Duellman, William E.; Trueb, Linda; Means, Bruce; D, Ross; Hedges, Blair" ;
    dc:date "2009" ;
    dc:title "A new frog family (Anura: Terrarana) from South America and an expanded direct-developing clade revealed by molecular phylogeny" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189874>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189875>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189876>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189880>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189877>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189878>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189879> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189874>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Dorsal view of female paratype of Ceuthomantis smaragdinus, KU 315000 SVL 19.5 mm. Arrows point to the dorsal glandlike structures. The third finger of the right hand is enlarged to show the notched anterior margin of the disc. Photographs by A. Campbell." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/189874/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189875>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views of the holotype of Ceuthomantis smaragdinus (KU 300000) in life. Photographs by D. B. Means." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/189875/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189876>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. High-resolution tomographs of Centhomantis smaragdinus, KU 315000. A dorsal, B. ventral. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/189876/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189880>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. High-resolution tomographs of terraranan frogs representing two families (left, dorsal view; right, ventral view). (A – B) Eleutherodactylidae, Eleutherodactylus gossei (SBH 266440; and (C – D) Strabomantidae, Pristimantis pulvinatus (KU 166368). Scale bars = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/189880/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189877>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Distribution of the family Ceuthomantidae. Lowlands are indicated by green and uplands by brown. Known localities of the new family are indicated in the northeastern and southwestern portions of elevated areas on the Guiana Shield, in Venezuela, Brazil, and Guyana. (1) Mt. Kopinang, Guyana (C. smaragdinus, type locality), (2) Mt. Ayanganna, Guyana C. smaragdinus, referred specimen), (3) Pico Tamacuari, Venezuela and Brazil (C. cavernibardus), (4) Cerro Aracamuni, Venezuela (C. aracamuni), and (5) Sarisariñama Tepui, Venezuela (C. cf. cavernibardus)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/189877/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189878>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Habitat of Ceuthomantis smaragdinus at 1540 m on Mt. Kopinang, Guyana. The holotype was found about 5 m from the stream in the foreground in Figure 5 A; the paratype was found on a leaf about 10 m away from the other side of the stream slightly to the left of the middle of Figure 5 B. Photographs by D. B. Means." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/189878/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.189879>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. High-resolution tomographs of terraranan frogs representing two families (left, dorsal view; right, ventral view). (A – B) Brachycephalidae, Ischnocnema guentheri (KU 92816); (C – D) Craugastoridae, Haddadus binotatus (KU 92808). Scale bars = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/189879/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

